<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF92FFFDFCC5FE8DFBD920DB" blockId="39.[827,1443,313,427]" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF92FFFDFCC5FE8DFC1F203E" box="[827,952,314,335]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF92FFFDFB76FE8DFA86203F" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1912" box="[1160,1313,313,335]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paraprotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="39" pageNumber="624" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atroluteus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF92FFFDFB76FE8DFA86203F" box="[1160,1313,313,335]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">P. atroluteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having carapace almost entirely coloured by a large, yellow spot, not occurring on ocularium (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF92FFFDFB41FEC1FAE320FD" box="[1215,1348,374,396]" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="39.[163,243,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,915,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-300@39.[323,1283,915,1794]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 28. Paraprotus albithorax, female holotype (SMF RII 132/2). A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. D, original label. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="39" pageNumber="624">Figs 28A–C</figureCitation>
). Tarsal counts: 7(3), 16(3), 10/11, 13.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF92FFFDFCC5FE7BFAC3236E" blockId="39.[827,1442,460,543]" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF92FFFDFCC5FE7BFC7F2090" box="[827,984,460,481]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">Distribution:</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="54D88838FF92FFFDFAFBFE7BFA9E2090" box="[1285,1337,460,481]" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">type</typeStatus>
locality. Eastern Cordillera real montane forest ecoregion in 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F878FF92FFFDFCC5FDBDFBD0236E" box="[827,1143,521,543]" country="Ecuador" name="Zamora-Chinchipe" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">Zamora Chinchipe Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFF92FFFDFB67FDBEFB5F236E" box="[1177,1272,521,543]" name="Ecuador" pageId="39" pageNumber="624">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF92FFFDFAF9FDBEFAF3236F" box="[1287,1364,521,543]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="35.[163,241,1281,1303]" captionTargetBox="[325,1281,197,1240]" captionTargetId="figure-292@35.[323,1283,195,1241]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 23. Map of known distribution of Paraprotus and Kayania. Numbers correspond to the following WWF ecoregions: 1 = Eastern Cordillera real montane forest, 2 = Ucayali moist forest, 3 = Peruvian yungas." pageId="39" pageNumber="624">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
